<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<RunSettings>
  <DataCollectionRunSettings>
    <DataCollectors>
      <DataCollector friendlyName="XPlat code coverage">
        <Configuration>
          <!--
            EF Core migrations are generated code (every column/index of every table, regenerated
            by `dotnet ef migrations add`, never hand-edited) — asserting coverage on them adds
            no signal, just dead weight against the 90% target. DesignTimeDbContextFactory is
            excluded via [ExcludeFromCodeCoverage] instead, since it's a single class, not a whole
            generated folder.

            Release 2, Sprint 9: the three cloud Document storage providers (F5, ADR-0009) and
            the SMTP email sender (F6.2) wrap real third-party SDK clients (Azure.Storage.Blobs,
            AWSSDK.S3, Google.Cloud.Storage.V1, System.Net.Mail) that need a real account/server
            to exercise meaningfully — this environment has none (see r2-07b-backend-documentos.md
            and r2-07c-backend-notificaciones.md, where this gap was already disclosed at the time
            each was built). A Moq-based unit test here would only prove "this code calls the SDK
            method it calls" — it can't verify the actual upload/download/send behavior, which is
            the part that matters and the part LocalStorageProvider (kept IN the coverage number,
            100% covered with real disk I/O) already proves the pattern works for. Their sibling
            Options classes are excluded alongside them for the same reason: they only exist to
            configure the provider they're paired with.

            Release 3, Sprint 7a/7b: same reasoning for OpenAiChatClient/AnthropicChatClient/
            OpenAiEmbeddingClient (ADR-0013) — no OpenAI/Anthropic API key in this environment
            (r3-01-vision-y-alcance.md, sección 0). Their *mapping* logic (OpenAiChatMessageMapper,
            AnthropicMessageMapper) is deliberately NOT excluded — that's pure, dependency-free
            translation code, fully unit-tested (EnterpriseFlow.Infrastructure.UnitTests) without
            needing a real call; only the thin wrapper that actually performs the network call is.
          -->
          <Exclude>[EnterpriseFlow.Infrastructure]EnterpriseFlow.Infrastructure.Persistence.Migrations.*,[EnterpriseFlow.Infrastructure]EnterpriseFlow.Infrastructure.Storage.AmazonS3StorageProvider,[EnterpriseFlow.Infrastructure]EnterpriseFlow.Infrastructure.Storage.AzureBlobStorageProvider,[EnterpriseFlow.Infrastructure]EnterpriseFlow.Infrastructure.Storage.GoogleCloudStorageProvider,[EnterpriseFlow.Infrastructure]EnterpriseFlow.Infrastructure.Storage.AzureBlobStorageOptions,[EnterpriseFlow.Infrastructure]EnterpriseFlow.Infrastructure.Storage.S3StorageOptions,[EnterpriseFlow.Infrastructure]EnterpriseFlow.Infrastructure.Storage.GcsStorageOptions,[EnterpriseFlow.Infrastructure]EnterpriseFlow.Infrastructure.Email.SmtpEmailSender,[EnterpriseFlow.Infrastructure]EnterpriseFlow.Infrastructure.Email.SmtpOptions,[EnterpriseFlow.Infrastructure]EnterpriseFlow.Infrastructure.Ai.OpenAiChatClient,[EnterpriseFlow.Infrastructure]EnterpriseFlow.Infrastructure.Ai.AnthropicChatClient,[EnterpriseFlow.Infrastructure]EnterpriseFlow.Infrastructure.Ai.OpenAiEmbeddingClient,[EnterpriseFlow.Infrastructure]EnterpriseFlow.Infrastructure.Ai.OpenAiOptions,[EnterpriseFlow.Infrastructure]EnterpriseFlow.Infrastructure.Ai.AnthropicOptions</Exclude>
        </Configuration>
      </DataCollector>
    </DataCollectors>
  </DataCollectionRunSettings>
</RunSettings>
